---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Consulting"
  description="Consulting, workshops and AI use analysis for organizations."
>
  <div class="lovable-page">
    <header class="lovable-page-hero consulting-hero">
      <div class="lovable-container">
        <div class="consulting-hero-grid">
          <div>
            <p class="eyebrow">Consulting</p>
            <h1>AI use analysis for organizations</h1>
            <p class="lede">
              Consulting, workshops and human-AI work principles for teams that want to
              use AI more deliberately.
            </p>
          </div>
          <aside class="consulting-side-note">
            <p class="small-label">Best fit</p>
            <p>
              Organizations starting to structure AI use, teams working with content,
              communication, education or creative workflows and leaders who need to
              understand the human side of AI adoption.
            </p>
          </aside>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <section class="lovable-section" aria-labelledby="services-title">
      <div class="lovable-container">
        <div class="lovable-section-header">
          <h2 id="services-title">What I help with</h2>
          <p>
            Practical, research-informed support for teams that need shared principles,
            verification habits and clearer human-AI workflows.
          </p>
        </div>
        <ol class="lovable-service-list">
          <li>
            <span>01</span>
            <h3>AI use analysis</h3>
            <p>I help map how teams currently use AI and where support is realistic.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span>02</span>
            <h3>Process mapping</h3>
            <p>I map tasks, information flow, handoffs and points where AI enters work.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span>03</span>
            <h3>Human-AI work model</h3>
            <p>I help design practical flows for what AI supports and what people own.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span>04</span>
            <h3>Team principles</h3>
            <p>I help teams create simple rules for trust, verification, data awareness and responsibility.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span>05</span>
            <h3>AI literacy</h3>
            <p>I build a common language for using generative tools without hype.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span>06</span>
            <h3>Workshops and talks</h3>
            <p>I run briefings, workshops and lectures on AI, cyberpsychology and Human-AI Interaction.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="lovable-section tinted-section" aria-labelledby="situations-title">
      <div class="lovable-container">
        <div class="compact-heading">
          <p class="eyebrow">Typical situations</p>
          <h2 id="situations-title">When this work is useful</h2>
        </div>
        <ol class="lovable-numbered-list">
          <li>A team uses AI, but everyone uses it differently.</li>
          <li>The organization wants to use AI, but has no shared principles.</li>
          <li>People paste sensitive information into tools without thinking through the risk.</li>
          <li>AI speeds up writing, but responsibility for the final output is unclear.</li>
          <li>Leaders do not know which tasks can be supported by AI.</li>
          <li>The organization wants practical internal AI use principles.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="lovable-section process-section" aria-labelledby="process-title">
      <div class="lovable-container">
        <div class="compact-heading">
          <p class="eyebrow">Process</p>
          <h2 id="process-title">How the collaboration can work</h2>
          <p>
            The format can stay compact, but I connect AI literacy with real tasks,
            risks and decision points.
          </p>
        </div>
        <ol class="process-line process-line-detailed" aria-label="Consulting process">
          <li><small>01</small><strong>Discovery</strong><span>where AI appears now and what the team needs to clarify</span></li>
          <li><small>02</small><strong>Process map</strong><span>which stages can be supported by AI and where handoffs happen</span></li>
          <li><small>03</small><strong>Risks and responsibility</strong><span>what requires verification, data awareness, control or another person</span></li>
          <li><small>04</small><strong>Human-AI work model</strong><span>what a sensible flow can look like in everyday work</span></li>
          <li><small>05</small><strong>Principles and next steps</strong><span>what to test, describe or clarify next</span></li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="lovable-section outcome-section" aria-labelledby="outcome-title">
      <div class="lovable-container outcome-grid">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">Outcome</p>
          <h2 id="outcome-title">What you can leave with</h2>
        </div>
        <ul class="outcome-list">
          <li>a map of current AI use in the team</li>
          <li>a list of processes where AI can support work</li>
          <li>areas that require caution, sources or another person</li>
          <li>simple principles for team AI use</li>
          <li>recommendations for verifying model outputs</li>
          <li>workshop notes or a short internal briefing for leaders or the team</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="lovable-container">
        <p class="disclaimer-line">
          Not legal advice. Not clinical advice. Not a promise of business outcomes.
          Not technical deployment work. Not shortcut-based prompt training.
        </p>
        <div class="consulting-actions">
          <a class="hero-button hero-button-primary" href="/contact/"><span aria-hidden="true"></span>Contact</a>
          <a class="hero-button hero-button-secondary" href="/concepts/">Read concepts</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
